Regarding tests: the tutorial from `numpy` is really the one you should take into account. On the other hand, including these test cases is usually enough:
- test against different combinations/types of input variables (e.g. check if `img` is really 2D as expected and an error is raised otherwise);
- test if function returns an expected output for some toy data: either compare the result with the one obtained using different pipeline, or compare with the pre-stored data;
- test if function performs in fixed and expected way for any boundary conditions / corner cases it has.

