the code above is generated with just a simple recursive application of `montage2d`, but I won't make a PR unless there is more interest or specific use cases. 
```python
def montage_nd(in_img):
    if len(in_img.shape)>3:
        return montage2d(np.stack([montage_nd(x_slice) for x_slice in in_img],0))
    elif len(in_img.shape)==3:
        return montage2d(in_img)
