@witsch, yes, setting `version_format` to something like `{tag}.dev{commitcount}` would bring us closer to what I am trying to accomplish, but it would still not be PEP440 compliant.  PEP440 is clear that [final releases](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0440/#id24) should only be in the form `x.y.z` -- and that is really what I would like to achieve for cleanliness.

The format `{tag}.dev{commitcount}` is still valid, but it is really intended for [development releases](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0440/#id27).

It doesn't sound like this is possible with `setuptools-git-version` at the moment -- correct me if I am wrong.  If this change is of value to others, I would be happy to put together a PR for this project.

